### a minimal version that fits into the flash of the device.       ###

INSTRUCTIONS TO INSTALL
________________________
If installing from the original firmware:
  1.- Plug your laptop to the router through ethernet cable.
  2.- Visit 192.168.0.1, default router IP.
  3.- Enter the default user/password: admin/admin.
  4.- Go to 'System Tools' -> 'Firmware Upgrade'
  5.- Select the image openwrt-ar71xx-generic-tl-wr841n-v9-squashfs-factory.bin
  6.- After the router is upgraded visit telnet to 192.168.1.1 and set a 
  password.
  7.- Install luci interface if needed, for that:
    1.- SSH into the device with the password set.
    2.- Edit the sources used by the router to update the software, editting 
      /etc/opkg.conf and enabling the line set for luci.
    3.- Execute 'opkg update'
    4.- Execute 'opkg install luci'

If installing from a existing openwrt version:
  1.- Plug your laptop to the router through ethernet cable.
  2.- Upload the file to the router executing:
    cat openwrt-ar71xx-generic-tl-wr841n-v9-squashfs-factory.bin | ssh \
    root@192.168.1.1 "cat - > /tmp/openwrt-ar71xx-generic-tl-wr841n-v9-squashfs-factory.bin"
  3.- Ensure that the MD5 of the file is: c116a93f9eb18a36d319de60ca99e1bd.
  4.- Execute 'cd /tmp'
  5.- Execute 'mtd -r write openwrt-ar71xx-generic-tl-wr841n-v9-squashfs-factory.bin firmware'
  6.- After the router is upgraded visit telnet to 192.168.1.1 and set a 
  password.
  7.- Install luci interface if needed, for that:
    1.- SSH into the device with the password set.
    2.- Edit the sources used by the router to update the software, editting 
      /etc/opkg.conf and enabling the line set for luci.
    3.- Execute 'opkg update'
    4.- Execute 'opkg install luci'

IMPORTANT NOTES
The flash memory of the device is pretty limited, select carefully the software 
you want to use.


For Dynamic DNS use: luci-app-ddns
 1.- opkg install luci-app-ddns
 2.- /etc/init.d/uhttpd restart
 3.- rm /tmp/luci-indexcache
